org.wisepersist.gwt.uploader.client

Class File

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.google.gwt.core.client.JavaScriptObject
      • org.wisepersist.gwt.uploader.client.File

  • public final class File
extends com.google.gwt.core.client.JavaScriptObject
    A logical bean that provides access to the details of a file being uploaded. An instance of this object is available on all uploader related event handlers, such as the UploadProgressHandler.

    Note that, by default, the SWFUpload "Speed" plugin is enabled, providing access to additional metrics on this object such as getAverageSpeed(), getPercentUploaded(), etc.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      static class  File.Status
      An enumeration of reported file status types, which can be determined during any of the uploader events, such as AbstractUploadEvent.getFile().

      • getCreationDate

        protected java.util.Date getCreationDate()
        Returns the date the file was created, as reported by the client machine. This method is purposefully hidden as it is available when the SWFUpload/Flash component is used, but is not available when the XMLHttpRequest Level 2 approach is used (which is the default). Please use the getModificationDate() method instead (which is available in both cases). Reference: http://www.w3.org/TR/file-uploader/#dfn-file
        Returns:
        Date
